../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-01.md:15:- "Define exactly what counts as preserved by Tao averaging and destroyed by Tao averaging" is only meaningful after fixing the level of comparison. Is the chain comparing identities, transport laws, closure estimates, compactness-compatible quantities, or actual contradiction mechanisms? Those are different tests. A property can fail as an exact identity and still survive at the estimate level that matters for regularity.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-01.md:18:- Hidden assumption: that there is one comparison granularity suitable for all candidate families. That is doubtful. Stochastic transport, deformation observables, and pressure identities do not naturally live at the same evidentiary level.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-01.md:26:- The candidate examples already preload the outcome: commutator-ready scalarization, deformation constraints, stochastic circulation, vorticity-direction persistence, pressure/stress identity. Those are familiar mission motifs, not a neutral search over "exact NS structures." The chain says "for example," but examples shape selection in practice.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-01.md:27:- Restricting to "mission-live sources only" is defensible for workflow discipline, but it creates a structural blind spot. If the mission's live sources are already biased toward Tao-sensitive geometric or transport-flavored mechanisms, this step cannot detect that the whole menu is path-dependent and incomplete.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-01.md:38:- Requiring one architecture per candidate is a strong anti-handwaving move. The problem is that the listed architectures are still broad labels: local criterion, transport-continuation, concentration exclusion, stochastic contradiction, critical-element rigidity. Each label hides several incompatible technical routes and bottlenecks.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-01.md:50:- The four axes are not commensurable. Tao sensitivity, endpoint closeness, prior-art distance, and narrowness of the first missing lemma measure different things and can point in opposite directions. A candidate close to an endpoint is often near prior art; a candidate far from prior art often has a very wide missing lemma. The chain offers no rule for handling these tradeoffs.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-008/attacks/chain-01.md:77:The chain compares objects that pay in different currencies: localized estimate gain, transport control, rigidity input, stochastic representation, concentration exclusion. Without a common evidentiary unit, a ranked atlas is mostly a polished preference ordering.
