../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/judgments/chain-02.md:5:The attacker is mostly correct. The original chain had real discipline compared with many speculative symbol-level programs: it fixed a narrow object class, imposed kill conditions, and explicitly worried about the usual failure mode that triad-level elegance disappears once one reconstructs the full equation. But it still left too much freedom early, especially around the theorem endpoint, the meaning of a "gain," and the quantitative size of any alleged helical advantage.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/judgments/chain-02.md:11:### 1. Step 1 is underconstrained because it does not fix the theorem-level endpoint early enough
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-005/judgments/chain-02.md:15:This is the central criticism. The original Step 1 let the chain choose among heterogeneous bottlenecks and heterogeneous gain currencies before committing to the exact estimate or contradiction point where the gain was supposed to matter. That invites retrofitting. The refined chain therefore requires, at the start, one theorem-level target inequality or contradiction point, one admissible solution framework, one representation, and one gain currency measured inside that target.
