../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:5:This chain is strongest as an obstruction hunt and weak as a positive proof route. Its good instinct is that full 3D Navier-Stokes transports more structure than energy alone, and that same-helicity folklore should not be confused with theorem-relevant leverage. Its main weakness is that it treats "joint energy-helicity flux" as if it were already a candidate coercive mechanism. It is not. Energy is positive and directly tied to standard control. Helicity is sign-indefinite, scale-weighted, and highly vulnerable to cancellation. Unless the chain can produce a one-sided, localization-stable, endpoint-relevant gain from that coupling, it is mostly repackaging cascade geometry.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:11:### Step 1 - Freeze one endpoint and one admissible invariant package
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:15:- The chain lets the user choose among several endpoints, but those endpoints demand very different kinds of leverage. A no-bad-cascade statement, an enstrophy-depletion estimate, and a contradiction on concentrated helicity-bearing regions are not interchangeable faces of one mechanism. Freezing one early risks selecting the endpoint that flatters the invariant package rather than the one the package can honestly touch.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:18:- The hidden assumption is that energy-helicity coupling contains an additional one-sided quantity that can face a regularity endpoint. But helicity density is sign-indefinite, and global helicity mixes scale and chirality rather than directly controlling the bad local term. That assumption should be tested before the endpoint is frozen, not after.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:19:- The minimum quantitative gain is underdefined. "Would change the endpoint" is too soft. The step should demand an explicit reduction of one named bad term or one explicit exclusion pattern. Without that, Step 1 can manufacture a polished setup memo around an invariant that has no coercive meaning.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:21:Failure mode: Step 1 locks in an attractive endpoint and ledger before establishing that helicity contributes anything beyond descriptive cascade language.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:28:- The Tao comparator is underspecified. What exact feature is the averaged model supposed to destroy: phase-sensitive triad geometry, sign-polarized transport, or a nontrivial coupling between scales and chirality? If that feature is not formalized before the comparison, "Tao-sensitive" will be backfilled from whatever survives the chosen decomposition.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:43:- The quantity "more than a thin favorable interaction class" is not operational. The relevant question is not whether the class is thin in an aesthetic sense, but whether it carries enough of the full nonlinear burden near the endpoint being targeted. Without that calibration, Step 3 can certify a regime that is large in one bookkeeping sense and irrelevant in theorem terms.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:53:- Localization is especially damaging here. Helicity is sign-indefinite, and local helicity budgets do not inherit the clean positivity that makes local energy machinery useful. Once cutoffs, flux commutators, and endpoint inequalities are inserted, the coupled-flux gain can evaporate immediately.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/attacks/chain-03.md:94:The premise already suggests that "the true 3D nonlinearity transports both energy and helicity" should hide a deeper invariant geometry. That is plausible as a heuristic, but it also biases the chain toward believing the coupling must mean more than it may actually mean. A fairer design would treat "exact but non-coercive" as the default hypothesis, not the backup hypothesis.
