../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/planner.md:16:Central premise: the mission may be closer to a publishable property map than to a single proof attack. The first admissible branch is therefore a direct structural comparison that ranks only those exact NS properties that are both truly destroyed by averaging and operational inside a named proof endpoint.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/planner.md:22:Central premise: the exact NS transport/stretching law may be more usable in material variables than in Eulerian estimate form. A live route would act through cumulative deformation, singular-value growth, or strain amplification along trajectories, not through local coefficient improvement.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/planner.md:24:Why it belongs now: this is transport-first without reverting to the dead neutral tube package. It asks whether the missing structure is the exact material amplification law itself.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/planner.md:34:Central premise: viscosity does not erase transport structure completely; it converts Kelvin/Cauchy-style identities into stochastic transport statements. If Tao-style averaging destroys the adapted stochastic backbone, this could be an NS-specific route unavailable to purely harmonic-analysis methods.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/planner.md:36:Why it belongs now: earlier Lagrangian and geometry branches were broad or tube-focused. This chain isolates the genuinely viscous transport representation instead of treating it as one item in a mixed bucket.
