../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-01.md:11:### Step 1 - Freeze one tensor representation and one bottleneck target
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-01.md:15:- The representation package is not the main unresolved choice. The real unresolved choice is the theorem-level endpoint. "Full stretching control," "pressure-Hessian/strain defect control," and "harmonic-moment cancellation" are not three versions of one bottleneck; they are three different proof architectures.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-01.md:18:- Freezing one representation this early may create representation loyalty. Once a package is chosen, later stages may start defending that package instead of asking whether the package ever exposed a coercive mechanism in the first place.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-01.md:20:The kill condition is too weak. A route can avoid collapsing to generic Calderon-Zygmund packaging and still be useless because the exact tensor representation has no one-sided inequality, no monotonicity, and no theorem endpoint attached to it.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-01.md:68:### 1. It still does not fix a theorem endpoint early enough
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-01.md:70:The chain freezes representation, bottleneck vocabulary, and observables before it fixes where the route is supposed to cash out mathematically. That invites post hoc success criteria. A tensor route should have to name the exact inequality, continuation criterion, or contradiction line before it starts optimizing observables.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/final-decider.md:17:- **Best execution fit for this system:** it can be driven by explicit objects, scenario classes, localization protocols, and kernel-level representations. That is a better match for disciplined stepwise analysis than the heavier global compactness-and-rigidity audit in Chain 03.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/final-decider.md:18:- **Strong useful floor on failure:** even a negative outcome can leave behind operational artifacts that matter for later work: an obstruction taxonomy, a representation-fixed failure analysis, and a hybrid observable ranking.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/final-decider.md:22:Chain 01 is the safest bounded obstruction branch, but it is too narrow to be the best next move. Its most credible endpoint is a cleanup memo showing that exact reformulations do not beat a fixed inherited bottleneck. That is useful, but it is less aligned with the mission's "beyond De Giorgi" ambition and has a lower novelty ceiling than the geometry route.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/final-decider.md:38:- **From both:** terminal claims must not outrun the exact observable family, scenario class, and representation actually audited.
