../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-02.md:23:- The separation into "exact structure," "Tao-sensitive structure," and "generic quadratic leftovers" is heavily representation-dependent. Helical coordinates are useful, but they also make bookkeeping artifacts look structural. The chain never states an invariant test for whether a feature is real or merely a basis effect.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-02.md:58:- The negative endpoint is better than nothing, but it still risks being too coarse. There is a difference between "single-triad signal does not survive shell summation," "survives on a sparse class but loses to multiplicity," and "requires localization whose cost exceeds the gain." Those are materially different obstructions.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-02.md:66:- The chain is symbol-first rather than bottleneck-first. It starts by choosing a representation and only later asks whether the chosen object actually touches a real theorem bottleneck. That encourages elegant algebra before strategic relevance.
