../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-03.md:5:This chain is disciplined about one real danger: accidentally reviving the dead De Giorgi machinery under Lorentz-space language. That is its best feature. Its main weakness is deeper: weak-type or Lorentz structure is a norm package, not an evident Navier-Stokes-specific mechanism. Under the mission's own Tao filter, that is a serious problem from the start, because weak-type Calderon-Zygmund, interpolation, and endpoint singular-integral technology are exactly the sort of harmonic-analysis assets the averaged model is meant to preserve.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-03.md:7:So the chain is strong as a bounded negative audit and weak as a positive research route. The likely honest output is not a theorem-like endpoint program, but an obstruction memo saying that once De Giorgi recursion is forbidden, the remaining weak-type package is either too generic, too soft under localization, or too non-mechanistic to drive contradiction.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-03.md:11:### Step 1 - Freeze anti-recursion guardrails and one endpoint target
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-03.md:15:- Freezing the forbidden moves is good discipline, but it does not identify what the replacement engine is. If there is no monotonicity, compactness-rigidity, exact commutator, geometric transport law, or other propagation mechanism, then "endpoint target" is just a rephrasing choice, not a route.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-03.md:16:- Choosing one endpoint target in advance is methodologically neat and mathematically risky. Weak-type local regularity, distribution-function control, and concentration bounds are not equivalent formulations of one live mechanism; they are different programs with different closure burdens. Freezing one too early invites narrative selection rather than evidence-driven selection.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-03.md:17:- The listed "gain currencies" are not sharp enough. `endpoint closure`, `distribution-tail decay`, and `localization-compatible weak-type control` are bookkeeping labels, not coercive quantities. A chain can claim progress in one of these currencies without having moved any blowup-relevant estimate.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-03.md:19:- The kill condition is underpowered. A target can avoid the literal old `U_k` recursion and still smuggle in the same architecture through epsilon-improvement loops, covering arguments, stopping-time decompositions, or endpoint bootstrap steps.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-03.md:27:- The proposed package is dominated by generic harmonic-analysis tools: weak-type Calderon-Zygmund bounds, Lorentz interpolation, endpoint pressure estimates. Under the mission context, that is already presumptively Tao-compatible, not a live source of NS-specific leverage.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-03.md:30:- The pressure part is especially suspect. Endpoint pressure estimates in Lorentz spaces sound differentiated, but pressure localization is exactly where cutoff commutators and decomposition debt tend to force one back into stronger spaces or non-endpoint control.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-03.md:31:- Prior-art overlap is not front-loaded enough. The mission context itself names Lorentz-space De Giorgi as an untested lead, but the broader endpoint-criterion literature is already crowded. Without an early novelty screen, Step 2 can rediscover known endpoint statements or known nonclosures and mistake that for branch-specific progress.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-03.md:35:### Step 3 - Build one non-De-Giorgi endpoint mechanism
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-03.md:39:- "Endpoint regularity criterion," "weak-type concentration inequality," and "localized pressure-transport control statement" are families of outcomes, not engines. None of them explains why weak-type information should propagate, sharpen, or contradict blowup.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-03.md:41:- The step asks how the mechanism differs from the old strong-type iteration, but "different from" is too weak. It must also be stronger than generic endpoint packaging and must exploit something NS-specific that the averaged model destroys.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-03.md:43:- The pressure-transport option is especially vulnerable to prior failure patterns. Once pressure and localization enter honestly, one is very close to the old burden stack, just stated in endpoint language rather than `U_k` language.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-03.md:45:Failure mode: Step 3 promotes a "mechanism" that is either a renamed endpoint criterion with no dynamic engine behind it or a pressure-localization package that quietly recreates the old debt in a new norm.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-03.md:54:- The four failure labels are useful but incomplete. There is a fifth important failure mode: no mechanism at all, only endpoint repackaging.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-03.md:55:- The step assumes that "survives unchanged in the averaged setting" can be assessed cleanly. In practice that comparison is often representation-dependent and easy to backfill after the fact unless the NS-specific feature was formalized earlier.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-03.md:57:Failure mode: Step 4 confirms, late and expensively, that the promoted route either never escaped generic endpoint analysis or collapses immediately when local weak-solution bookkeeping is charged honestly.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-03.md:59:### Step 5 - Promote only an earned endpoint claim
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-03.md:63:- If a positive statement survives to this point, the "first missing lemma" is very likely to be the whole problem in compressed form: an NS-specific coercive step that turns generic endpoint control into actual blowup exclusion. The chain understates that risk.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-03.md:64:- A theorem-like conditional program can be misleading here. It is easy to write a clean endpoint proposition whose hypothesis already smuggles in strong-type control, an epsilon-regularity gain, or a hidden iteration mechanism.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-03.md:90:The route sits next to endpoint regularity criteria, Lorentz refinements, and weak-space formulations that have been studied for years. Because the chain is framed at the level of architecture rather than a sharply new identity or monotonic quantity, it is especially vulnerable to rediscovering known statements or known reasons they do not close.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-006/attacks/chain-03.md:105:As a falsification program for the Lorentz or weak-type lead named in the mission context, this chain is good. As a serious positive route beyond De Giorgi, it is weak. The main reason is not that endpoint ideas are impossible; it is that this chain never identifies a Navier-Stokes-specific mechanism that weak-type packaging would carry. Without that, it is mostly an audit of whether generic endpoint harmonic analysis can be made to look more structural than it is.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-01.md:5:The attacker is mostly right. The original chain is disciplined and worth keeping, but only as a narrowly scoped obstruction branch, not as a broad discovery program for the mission's beyond-De-Giorgi mechanism. Its main strengths are real: it asks for estimate-level gains, it front-loads killing cosmetic rewrites, and it is willing to end negatively. Its main weaknesses are also real: it leaves the target architecture under-specified, states the Tao screen too loosely, treats geometry too much as contamination, and makes the negative endpoint easier to earn than the positive one.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-01.md:35:### 4. The negative endpoint is structurally easier to earn than the positive endpoint
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-01.md:41:So the refinement must make the endpoint explicit: a bounded obstruction statement on a specified architecture and candidate family counts as success, but nothing broader is earned.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-01.md:85:The negative endpoint also has to be tightly phrased. At best, this branch can rule out a specified family of exact reformulations relative to one fixed architecture, not reformulation gains in general.
