../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-02.md:13:The attack is right that the Tao/NS-specificity filter is not operational enough as written. "Identify the exact ingredient" is still too impressionistic unless each candidate ingredient is translated into a concrete benchmark against averaged-model robustness and against known geometric regularity mechanisms. The critique is also right that transport laws, algebraic identities, and multiscale coherence mechanisms should not be mixed without separate tests.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-02.md:39:### 6. Step 3 uses non-canonical decompositions without fixing a representation
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-02.md:43:This is one of the attack's strongest points. A negative conclusion about a "nonlocal remainder" is not reliable unless the chain first fixes a kernel-level representation of `S omega . omega` and a localization protocol. Otherwise the remainder can be an artifact of the chosen split.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-02.md:49:The attacker is correct. `u x omega` is not the stretching term. Its appearance in the Step 3 kill condition weakens confidence that the target mechanism has been fixed sharply enough. The refined chain should remove that language and focus only on representations of `S omega . omega`.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-02.md:55:The attacker is right that dynamic plausibility should constrain observable design much earlier. In this area, propagation is often the bottleneck. Observables with no credible transport or persistence story should be downgraded before the chain invests heavily in static estimates.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-02.md:61:Demanding an explicit transport identity or coercive persistence mechanism is appropriate as a high bar for a final positive route. But the attacker is right that using that bar as a blanket veto can misclassify informative partial mechanisms as failures. The refined chain should use persistence as an early screening and ranking device, with a stricter bar only at the final promotion stage.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-02.md:79:The chain is intentionally obstruction-first, and that is not itself a flaw. But the accumulation of early kill conditions, undefined terms, and decomposition freedom does create a procedural bias toward a polished negative memo. The refined chain should keep the obstruction discipline while delaying terminal judgments until the observables, scenario, and stretching representation are fixed.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-02.md:85:This is a real issue. Because the chain sits directly in an area with substantial prior work, it needs explicit calibration against Constantin-Fefferman-Majda, later vorticity-direction coherence work, and related geometric depletion or near-Beltrami discussions before claiming novelty or NS-specificity.
../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-002/judgments/chain-02.md:103:- fix a kernel-level stretching representation before speaking of a nonlocal remainder;
