../../planning-runs/run-008/judgments/chain-03.md:5:The attack is mostly correct. The original chain identifies a genuinely different structural reservoir: exact stochastic transport and martingale formulas for Navier-Stokes are not interchangeable with standard Eulerian energy estimates. That is a real positive. But the attack is right that the chain delays the decisive question for too long: whether one exact stochastic observable yields coercive, localizable, endpoint-relevant control rather than an elegant reformulation.
../../planning-runs/run-008/judgments/chain-03.md:19:The attack is right that the original menu of stochastic objects and endpoints was too broad and too easy to backfill after the fact. It is also right that the chain should screen for non-coercivity, expectation-only content, and unusable localization much earlier. But some early freezing is still good method. The correction is not to avoid early choices; it is to freeze the blowup mechanism, candidate observable, and admissibility rules before final endpoint selection.
../../planning-runs/run-008/judgments/chain-03.md:34:This is the real bottleneck, and the original chain left too much heavy lifting for it. The attack is also right that a bare martingale bound is not enough unless it controls a named concentration or stretching quantity, and that importing a stronger framework can be parasitic if it merely smuggles back the deterministic hard part.
../../planning-runs/run-008/judgments/chain-03.md:66:### Structural weakness 6 - solution-class issue treated too narrowly
../../planning-runs/run-008/judgments/chain-03.md:69:Correct. The issue is not only formal availability of a representation. The deeper question is whether it remains usable near the intended singular regime without relying on smooth flows, filtration assumptions, or localization/stopping constructions that collapse precisely where the branch hopes to say something.
../../planning-runs/run-008/judgments/chain-03.md:76:- Front-load prior-art, solution-class, stopping-time, and localization screens.
