../../../../missions/beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-008/judgments/chain-03.md:5:The attack is mostly correct. The original chain identifies a genuinely different structural reservoir: exact stochastic transport and martingale formulas for Navier-Stokes are not interchangeable with standard Eulerian energy estimates. That is a real positive. But the attack is right that the chain delays the decisive question for too long: whether one exact stochastic observable yields coercive, localizable, endpoint-relevant control rather than an elegant reformulation.
