../../../../runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-run-004-judge-03.log:170:- The examples given are all familiar suspects: eigenvalue gaps, alignment, misalignment, harmonic-defect quantities. That is not disqualifying, but it means the chain is heavily exposed to prior-art redundancy. Without an explicit literature checkpoint, this step can rediscover Constantin-Fefferman style alignment heuristics, pressure-Hessian closure ideas, or restricted-Euler motifs and mislabel them as new leads.
../../../../runtime/logs/codex-patlas-beyond-de-giorgi-strategizer-step-011.log:2085:../../../beyond-de-giorgi/planning-runs/run-007/planner-chains/chain-04.md:5:Viscosity does not destroy transport structure completely; it replaces deterministic Kelvin/Cauchy laws with stochastic transport identities. This chain asks whether one exact stochastic circulation or back-to-label object yields theorem-relevant control that Tao's averaged model would not preserve.
