- [VERIFIED] `L^3` and `\dot H^{1/2}` are serious only as ambiguous critical-space languages, not as frozen frameworks.
- [VERIFIED] `BMO^{-1}` is excluded up front unless the branch can supply a large-data replacement compactness package, which the repository does not provide.
- [VERIFIED] The run-005 selection logic keeps `Chain 01` as the canonical next branch, but that branch is explicitly a falsification-first compactness-rigidity audit, not evidence that a new framework has been earned.
- [VERIFIED] `Chain 02` and `Chain 03` are alternate attack routes, not replacements for the frozen LEI architecture. They do not supply a new solution framework here.

## Frozen Baseline

The inherited baseline is now fixed as follows:

- [VERIFIED] suitable weak solutions in the Leray-Hopf energy class;
- [VERIFIED] the local energy inequality for every nonnegative compactly
  supported test function;
- [VERIFIED] divergence-free velocity, `u in L^\infty_t L^2_x \cap L^2_t H^1_x`;
- [VERIFIED] pressure handled in the suitable-weak sense;
- [VERIFIED] the localized LEI cutoff-flux bundle `I_flux[phi] = ∬ (|u|^2 + 2p) u . nabla phi`;
- [VERIFIED] the CKN scale-invariant quantities `A(r)`, `E(r)`, `C(r)`, and
  `D(r)` as the fixed local-energy bookkeeping language.

This is the compatibility floor. The branch may continue only inside this floor
unless a new architecture is explicitly proved and named, which the local
record does not do.

