+   backward-flow / back-to-label structure,
+   or only a generic literature neighborhood?
+2. What exact gain is already standard there on the repository record?
+3. What exact beyond-baseline gain would the present branch need so that it is
+   not just replaying a known exact-but-nonclosing stochastic reformulation?
+4. Can the anti-repackaging rule be stated concretely in this branch’s own
+   burden language, especially around expectation-only control, filtration
+   bookkeeping, and imported stronger frameworks?
+5. Does the branch already fail here because the local record never gets beyond
+   comparator naming without a usable theorem-facing gap?
+
+## Working Hypotheses To Test, Not Assume
+
+- `Constantin-Iyer representation term` is the nearest explicit comparator
+  because it is the only stochastic name frozen in the planning archive.
+- The repository supports the existence of a known failure pattern
+  (`exact stochastic reformulation -> expectation/localization nonclosure`) more
+  strongly than it supports any concrete beyond-prior-art gain.
+- The right anti-repackaging rule is:
+  stochastic elegance does not count if the usable content is only the
+  deterministic burden rewritten through expectation, filtration, or imported
+  regularity machinery.
+
+Confirm, refine, or reject these hypotheses from source-backed evidence.
