+# Exploration 001 Goal
+
+## Objective
+
+Freeze one honest mechanism-family-observable triple for the stochastic branch,
+or say plainly that the repository leaves only a representation menu rather than
+a concrete Step-1 setup.
+
+This exploration is responsible for:
+
+- one named bad term or blowup mechanism;
+- one primary stochastic representation family only;
+- one candidate observable;
+- and one brief explanation of why that family is the best first test for that
+  mechanism.
+
+## Required Questions
+
+Answer all of the following from local repository materials:
+
+1. Which burden is the sharpest honest first target on the local record:
+   vortex-stretching growth,
+   local concentration of active scales,
+   loss of control along advected filaments,
+   or another more precise bad term actually supported on disk?
+2. Which stochastic family is best supported as a first test for that burden:
+   stochastic Kelvin circulation,
+   stochastic Cauchy / back-to-label / backward-flow transport,
+   or a martingale observable adapted to stretching or concentration?
+3. What exact candidate observable is the most concrete on the repository
+   record?
+4. Does the evidence support a real mechanism-facing triple, or only planning
+   language that never exits representational variety?
+5. If one triple is still honest, what would count as a real gain on that
+   burden and what would already fail as expectation-only or rhetorical
+   packaging?
+
+## Working Hypotheses To Test, Not Assume
+
+- The branch, if it survives at all, should prioritize `local concentration of
+  active scales` over a continuation criterion because the run-008 judgment
+  repeatedly treats local concentration exclusion as the default endpoint and
+  continuation as too coercive for early admission.
+- The most plausible family on disk is a `backward stochastic flow /
+  Constantin-Iyer style` transport object rather than a generic martingale,
+  because that is the only comparator neighborhood named explicitly in the
+  planning record.
+- The local record may still fail to freeze a real observable beyond names like
+  `stochastic circulation identity` or `back-to-label observable`.
+
+Confirm, refine, or reject these hypotheses from source-backed evidence.
+
+## Success Criteria
+
+- Produce one table with columns:
+  `item`, `frozen choice`, `status`, `support`, `why this beats nearby options`.
+- Label major claims `[VERIFIED]`, `[INFERRED]`, or `[PROPOSED]`.
+- End with one explicit conclusion:
+  `one mechanism-family-observable triple is freezeable`, or
+  `scope lock remains menu-level`.
+
+## Failure Criteria
+
+- The report keeps multiple stochastic families alive as co-primaries.
+- The report chooses a mechanism or observable that appears only as generic
+  branch rhetoric.
+- The report treats Tao distinctness as a substitute for mechanism-facing gain.
